OL,6,FAnyone with even a rudimentary
OL,7,Funderstanding of how the BBC works
OL,8,Fwill be aware of how the chairman is
OL,9,Fwell removed from editorial and
OL,10,Fcreative decision-making.
OL,12,FSimilar claims were made in the past
OL,13,Fabout governments sending in chairmen
OL,14,Fto "sort out" the BBC ` from Lord
OL,15,FHill to Marmaduke Hussey.
OL,17,FBut somehow the BBC has to enjoy the
OL,18,Fconfidence of everyone in the land `
OL,19,Fthrough all shades of mainstream
OL,20,Fpolitical opinion and beyond.
OL,3,CImpartiality and the BBC in the age
