OL,6,FTo say it can be a challenge and a
OL,7,Fnightmare is an understatement.
OL,9,FFor some critics, the fact a story
OL,10,Fdid not run on the BBC News at Six
OL,11,Fmeans the BBC itself did not or would
OL,12,Fnot cover it ` even if that story
OL,13,Factually ran on, say, the News at Ten
OL,14,For featured  prominently online.
OL,16,FOthers imagine preconceived left or
OL,17,Fright wing bias, misinterpret
OL,18,Finclusivity as wokeness, see a
OL,19,Fconcern to attract younger audiences
OL,20,Fto some services as meaning that
OL,21,Folder people don't matter. The list
OL,22,Fgoes on.
OL,3,CImpartiality and the BBC in the age
OL,4,Cof social media
